newsArray.title: PSL 2025 Points Table, Most Runs & Most Wickets List After Multan Sultans vs Lahore Qalandars Match
creator: ABP Live Sports
newsArray.description: Lahore Qalandars (LQ) defeated Multan Sultans (MS) by five wickets in the 16th match of the ongoing Pakistan Super League (PSL) 2025 season on April 26 (Saturday). After winning the toss and opting to field, Lahore restricted Multan to 185/3. Multan captain Mohammad Rizwan anchored the innings with an unbeaten 76 off 48 balls (six fours, three sixes), while Kamran Ghulam supported with an unbeaten 52 off 31 balls (two fours, four sixes). For Lahore, Tom Curran impressed with figures of 1/24 from four overs, while Shaheen Afridi finished with 0/25. Multan struck early with the ball, reducing Lahore to 45/2 in 6.1 overs. However, Abdullah Shafique (34 off 25) and Daryl Mitchell (64 off 37) steadied the chase. Even after Ubaid Shah (2/34) picked up two quick wickets to leave Lahore at 95/4, Sikandar Raza's unbeaten 40 off just 21 balls helped the hosts seal the win. Mitchell and Raza shared an 89-run partnership off just 44 deliveries.With this victory, Lahore Qalandars climbed to second place on the PSL 2025 points table, ahead of Karachi Kings on net run rate (+0.543 compared to KK's -0.217), despite both teams having six points. newsArray.title: PSL X: Peshawar Zalmi lock horns with Quetta Gladiators at Lahore’s Qaddafi Stadium
creator: fatimah.amjad
newsArray.description: article author: Shahjahan KhurramAuthor: Sun, 2025-04-27 19:03LAHORE: Peshawar Zalmi won the toss and chose to bowl first against Quetta Gladiators in the 17th match of the Pakistan Super League 10th edition (PSL X) at Qaddafi Stadium in Lahore on Sunday.Zalmi have lost three of their four matches this season and secured their only win over Multan Sultans. All eyes have been on Zalmi skipper Babar Azam, who has been consistently performing in PSL X, in Sunday’s encounter against Gladiators.Zalmi said it was “time to shine” in a post on Instagram as their skipper said they were going in with a clear approach.Main category: SportPakistanTags: Peshawar ZalmiPSL XQaddafi Stadium

newsArray.title: PSL 2025 Points Table, Most Runs & Most Wickets List After Multan Sultans vs Lahore Qalandars Match
creator: ABP Live Sports
newsArray.description: Lahore Qalandars (LQ) defeated Multan Sultans (MS) by five wickets in the 16th match of the ongoing Pakistan Super League (PSL) 2025 season on April 26 (Saturday). After winning the toss and opting to field, Lahore restricted Multan to 185/3. Multan captain Mohammad Rizwan anchored the innings with an unbeaten 76 off 48 balls (six fours, three sixes), while Kamran Ghulam supported with an unbeaten 52 off 31 balls (two fours, four sixes). For Lahore, Tom Curran impressed with figures of 1/24 from four overs, while Shaheen Afridi finished with 0/25. Multan struck early with the ball, reducing Lahore to 45/2 in 6.1 overs. However, Abdullah Shafique (34 off 25) and Daryl Mitchell (64 off 37) steadied the chase. Even after Ubaid Shah (2/34) picked up two quick wickets to leave Lahore at 95/4, Sikandar Raza's unbeaten 40 off just 21 balls helped the hosts seal the win. Mitchell and Raza shared an 89-run partnership off just 44 deliveries.With this victory, Lahore Qalandars climbed to second place on the PSL 2025 points table, ahead of Karachi Kings on net run rate (+0.543 compared to KK's -0.217), despite both teams having six points. newsArray.title: PSL X: Peshawar Zalmi lock horns with Quetta Gladiators at Lahore’s Qaddafi Stadium
creator: fatimah.amjad
newsArray.description: article author: Shahjahan KhurramAuthor: Sun, 2025-04-27 19:03LAHORE: Peshawar Zalmi won the toss and chose to bowl first against Quetta Gladiators in the 17th match of the Pakistan Super League 10th edition (PSL X) at Qaddafi Stadium in Lahore on Sunday.Zalmi have lost three of their four matches this season and secured their only win over Multan Sultans. All eyes have been on Zalmi skipper Babar Azam, who has been consistently performing in PSL X, in Sunday’s encounter against Gladiators.Zalmi said it was “time to shine” in a post on Instagram as their skipper said they were going in with a clear approach.Main category: SportPakistanTags: Peshawar ZalmiPSL XQaddafi Stadium
